data.description: SCENIC GOLF COURSE VIEW! Bright and spacious 3 bedroom/2 bath in the highly desired Groves Golf and Country Club community. Home includes "library/den/office" in master suite, 2-car garage "with golf cart garage".  Great entertaining home with large kitchen that flows into the family room. The family room overlooks an oversized lanai with a pool and beautiful golf course and water view. The kitchen has stainless steel appliances with a double oven range and, eat-in kitchen. A custom designed Wine & Coffee bar has both wine and beverage refrigerators in kitchen. Easy care laminate and tile floors throughout the home. Elegant decorative fans and lighting. Master bedroom suite has large library/office/den for complete privacy. Huge walk-in closet, bathroom has soaker tub, walk-in shower and dual sinks complete the ensuite. Airy and bright second bedroom easily holds a queen bed and dresser.  The third bedroom has a murphy bed to be included with sale.  Additionally Custom “Closets by Design” in master suite, pantry, laundry and library.  This home has a 920 sq.ft. lanai with pool and pavers overlooking the 16th fairway of the golf course. Bring your friends to enjoy this stunning outdoor living space.  The front door has a phantom screen.  Bedrooms all have faux wood blinds. The garage has 3 "Safe Racks" ceiling storage racks and built-in cabinets. ROOF REPLACED NOV 2020. The Groves is a gated, active adult golf course community with heated pool and spa, tennis courts, bocce courts, shuffleboard, clubhouse, fitness center, library, craft room, party room and restaurant.  Shopping center with Publix grocery store outside gate.  Close to everything including dining, shopping and health care! Close to Tampa Premium Outlet Mall and easy access via Veterans Expressway to Tampa International Airport.
